@NODE Introducing "Introducing Guide2Doc"
@TOC Main

    @{b}Guide2Doc@{ub} converts AmigaGuide files in plain text files by
removing the AmigaGuide commands or replacing them with another string.
Guide2Doc is useful to make a printable copy of an AmigaGuide file and for
me that's it's only purpose.

  Node <name> <title> commands are replaced by a paperfeed and some lines 
    this ensures the printer takes a new paper for the next node.

  \@{i} \@{ub} ....  sequences are replaced by a user definable string and
    default are replaced by nothing.

  \@{" some text " Link "some text"} are replaced by 'some text'

  All other AmigaGuide command sequences are removed from the file.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Requirements "System Requirements"
@TOC Main

    @{b}Guide2Doc@{ub} should run on any Amiga system with at least 512K
RAM and one disk-drive.  @{b}Guide2Doc@{ub} requires KickStart v2.04 or
higher to run and is currently a CLI only program.

    @{b}Guide2Doc@{ub} also requires the ReqTools.library v38 or higher.
ReqTools is copyright 1993 by Nico FranÓois.

    Should you have any trouble running @{b}Guide2Doc@{ub} on your machine, please
@{"write to me" LINK Author} with the full specifications of your machine, that is KickStart
version, model, expansion boards etc...

@ENDNODE
@NODE Usage "How to use Guide2Doc"
@TOC Main
    @{b}Guide2Doc@{ub} can be started from the Shell or the Workbench.

    CLI usage:

      Guide2Doc F=FROM/M/A,TO/A,O=OVERWRITE/S,N=NEWLINE/S,
                         STYLEON/K,STYLEOFF/K

      OVERWRITE      : overwrite existing without confirmation.
      NEWLINE        : add newline before new nodes (never before Main).
      STYLEON string : styles on sequences will replaced by the supplied string
      STYLEOFF string: styles off sequences will replaced by the supplied string

      The keyword FROM is not needed and specifies which files must be converted. 
      The FROM files can be specified by using the Amiga's pattern
      matching capabilities.

      The keyword TO is not needed if the target name is put after the from
      files.  The keyword TO specifies the target and can or must (multiple
      FROM's) be a directory. In this last case the created file will have the
      same name as the FROM file and will be put in the TO directory.

      If FROM and TO file are the same the FROM file will be overwritten
      with the converted file.

    WB usage:

      Tooltypes:

        STYLEON=string (text styles on sequences will replaced by the supplied string)

        STYLEOFF=string (text styles off sequences will replaced by the supplied string)

        NEWLINE=YES | NO

        OVERWRITE=YES | NO

      Method 1:
        Select Guide2Doc and shift double click the files to convert.
        For every icon Guide2Doc asks a new name.

      Method 2:
        Double click Guide2Doc, a file requester appears, select .guide file.
        Guide2Doc then asks a new name for the converted file.

@ENDNODE
